A Dutch judge ruled Friday that the alleged killer of filmmaker Theo van Gogh should remain in custody for another 10 days together with four other North African men accused of belonging to a "terrorist conspiracy", the ANP news agency said.
Police detained an additional suspect in the slaying of Dutch filmmaker Theo van Gogh and arrested two other men accused of calling for the beheading of a politician in a video circulating on the Internet, prosecutors said Saturday.
